sentences: It's been a clinical performance from Sydney Thunder today.
Having put a good looking total on the board, their bowlers came charging at the Sixers and never allowed easy runs.
The pressure of mounting run-rate eventually got the better of the Sixers who perished while trying to up the ante.
Russel was phenomenal in the beginning and bowled in the right areas, he was amply supported by bowlers from the other end.
Shane Watson proved that he still has it in him and selectors cannot ignore him.
The hosts had a forgettable season last time around but having started this one on a winning note, they would like to go the distance.
That's it from us today.
Don't forget to join us tomorrow for the second game of the  .
6 BBL.
Bye, take care!Hussey (Man of the Match): 'Yeah we are having a balance in the squad and there is variety in the team.
We are lucky to have so many all-rounders in the team.
It's tough work and we are determined to do the job.
One end played quite well but the other end was on a bit slower side.
We looked to capitalise on that and it came good for us.'
McKay to Bollinger, out Caught by Kallis!!

Chris Green will open the attackWelcome back..Thanks to Hussey, Thunder have posted a good total on the board, they would have liked to have 15 more but wickets during the middle of the innings cost them that.
Though they cannot complain as Sixers dropped a couple of dollies in the middle and that helped Thunder pace their innings.
It's a good total on this track and Thunder would hope that their bowlers are able to defend.
Join us in a while as we bring you the chase... .

The Thunder are hosting the Sixers at the Sydney Showground stadium.
History hasn't been kind for the hosts, with their performances being rather modest.
But this is the start of a new season and they will enter into the competition with high hopes.
Mike Hussey will be leading the outfit, which also includes Jacques Kallis and Shane Watson.

On the other hand, the Sixers will miss the star presence of Mitchell Starc, but have a host of players who are more than capable of winning a match on their own.The Big Bash is back and it's going to be another season of high octane drama and excitement.

The best players across Australia and the cream of international stars make this one of the blockbuster T20 tournaments going around - perhaps the best after the Indian Premier League (in terms of crowd attendence).
It was all Scorchers last season, with the Perth franchise running away as deserving winners.
Will they continue to steamroll opposition this time around as well?
They have competition, the two Melbourne and Sydney franchises are desperate for silver ware, while Brisbane, Adelaide and Hobart aren't too far behind either.
It promises to be an action packed summer of cricket.

Stay tuned as we bring you each and every bit of action, right from the first to the last ball of the tournament.Preview:

The fifth edition of the Big Bash League (BBL) can be a season of redemption for Sydney Thunder when they take on Sydney Sixers at the Spotless Stadium in Sydney in the first match of the  .
6 season on Thursday (December 17).
Thunder have had a dismal record in the previous seasons, winning just five of their 30 games, and it isn't surprising that they've finished at the bottom of the table thrice.
Thunder have played seven times in the past against the Sixers, losing all the games, and curtailing this 'record' could well be motivation that the team is looking for.
In a tournament like Big Bash, it's important that the teams gain momentum right from the beginning.
Sydney Thunder made a promising start last season as well.
They hammered the Brisbane Heat but failed to carry on and were able to register just one more win that season.
However, with Shane Watson, Andre Russell, Jacques Kallis and Michael Hussey in their ranks, they have a good mix of power-hitters and accumulators.
It will be interesting to see if Usman Khawaja, who is recovering from a hamstring injury, gets a game.
Khawaja's performance could also determine if he'll start in the playing XI against West Indies in the Boxing Day Test.
The Australian selectors will also be keeping an eye on Watson with the series against India and the ICC World Twenty20 approaching.

For Watson personally, this will be a good opportunity to show the Indian Premier League franchises that he still has it in him as a limited-overs player after the all-rounder was ignored by the new teams - Pune and Rajkot - in the IPL players draft.

The Sixers will miss the services of Steve Smith, who has decided to rest ahead of the Boxing Day Test because of niggles, and Mitchell Starc, who is out with an injured foot and it also likely to miss the World T20 next year.
Josh Hazelwood is also unlikely to feature in the playing XI after the national team think-tank decided to manage his work load keeping the busy schedule ahead in mind.
The Sixers have a power packed batting line-up with Nic Maddinson, Michael Lumb and Brad Haddin in their ranks.
Though they'll miss a few key players, the bowling still can knock out any opposition.
Doug Bollinger, Johan Botha, Sean Abbott and Moises Henriques, the all-rounder, will decide how things shape up for the team.
The squad also signed up Li Kai Ming, the Hong Kong legspinner, as a community rookie.
Though he isn't part of the squad, he can be included as a replacement player.
Solomon Mire, who was signed as a community rookie player two season ago, was included in the Melbourne Renegades as the season progressed.
A drop-in pitch will be used for the game and Hussey seemed pretty confident that it will be a good wicket.
"We h practice out there last night and the pitch played really well," Hussey said ahead of the game.
"We've actually got the two pitches from the ANZ Stadium over, and they played really well last year.
We're hoping for just a good track, really."
"It's a great acquisition for the Thunder to make sure we have a bit of a home-town advantage, knowing what the wickets are going to do," pointed out Watson.
On paper, the Sixers look more formidable but if the seasoned campaigners can step up for Thunder, we are in for a cracking contest.
